, sort, and heap, within the broader topic of binary heap.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Is Apply Operations to Maximize Score good for interviews?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Yes — as a Hard problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\\\"}},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Question\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Where can I read the official statement?\\\",\\\"acceptedAnswer\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Answer\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\\\"}}]}\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"14:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"container-af py-8\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Article\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"headline\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Original Hard explanation for Apply Operations to Maximize Score (LeetCode #2818). Pattern: stack. Time O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), space O(sqrt(r) + n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"url\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"author\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"AlgoForge\\\\\\\"},\\\\\\\"publisher\\\\\\\":{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Organization\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"AlgoForge\\\\\\\"},\\\\\\\"datePublished\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-01-01\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"dateModified\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"2026-07-17\\\\\\\"}\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$1d\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowTo\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"How to solve Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"description\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Original Hard explanation for Apply Operations to Maximize Score (LeetCode #2818). Pattern: stack. Time O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), space O(sqrt(r) + n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"step\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Implement the stack, greedy, sort, and heap approach\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":4,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":5,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":6,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"HowToStep\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":7,\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"nav\\\",null,{\\\"aria-label\\\":\\\"Breadcrumb\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"script\\\",null,{\\\"type\\\":\\\"application/ld+json\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"@context\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://schema.org\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"itemListElement\\\\\\\":[{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":1,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Home\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":2,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Problems\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\\\\\"},{\\\\\\\"@type\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"ListItem\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"position\\\\\\\":3,\\\\\\\"name\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\\\\\",\\\\\\\"item\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\\\\\"}]}\\\"}}],\\\"$L1e\\\"]}],\\\"$L1f\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"20:I[56303,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"BookmarkButton\\\"]\\n21:I[705747,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"CodeTabs\\\"]\\n1e:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"ol\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[false,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Home\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/problems\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"aria-hidden\\\":true,\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-border\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"/\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Problems\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"li\\\",\\\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\",{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-1.5\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"aria-hidden\\\":true,\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-border\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"/\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground font-medium\\\",\\\"aria-current\\\":\\\"page\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\"}]]}]]}]\\n22:T11a6,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"// Time:  O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + pi(sqrt(r))) + klogn) = O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), m is max(k for _, k in queries), pi(n) = number of primes in a range [1, n] = O(n/logn) by prime number theorem, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number_theorem\\n// Space: O(sqrt(r) + n)\\n\\n// number theory, mono stack, greedy, sort, heap\\nclass Solution {\\npublic:\\n    int maximumScore(vector\\u003cint\\u003e\\u0026 nums, int k) {\\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\\n        const auto\\u0026 addmod = [\\u0026](uint32_t a, uint32_t b) {  // avoid overflow\\n            a %= MOD, b %= MOD;\\n            if (MOD - a \\u003c= b) {\\n                b -= MOD;  // relied on unsigned integer overflow in order to give the expected results\\n            }\\n            return a + b;\\n        };\\n\\n        const auto\\u0026 mulmod = [\\u0026](uint32_t a, uint32_t b)  {  // avoid overflow\\n            a %= MOD, b %= MOD;\\n            uint32_t result = 0;\\n            if (a \\u003c b) {\\n                swap(a, b);\\n            }\\n            while (b \\u003e 0)  { \\n                if (b % 2 == 1) {\\n                    result = addmod(result, a);\\n                }\\n                a = addmod(a, a);\\n                b /= 2; \\n            } \\n            return result; \\n        };\\n\\n        const auto\\u0026 powmod = [\\u0026](uint32_t a, uint32_t b) {\\n            a %= MOD;\\n            uint32_t result = 1;\\n            while (b) {\\n                if (b \\u0026 1) {\\n                    result = mulmod(result, a);\\n                }\\n                a = mulmod(a, a);\\n                b \\u003e\\u003e= 1;\\n            }\\n            return result;\\n        };\\n    \\n        const auto\\u0026 linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes = [](int n) {  // Time: O(n), Space: O(n)\\n            vector\\u003cint\\u003e spf(n + 1, -1);\\n            vector\\u003cint\\u003e primes;\\n            for (int i = 2; i \\u003c= n; ++i) {\\n                if (spf[i] == -1) {\\n                    spf[i] = i;\\n                    primes.emplace_back(i);\\n                }\\n                for (const auto\\u0026 p : primes) {\\n                    if (i * p \\u003e n || p \\u003e spf[i]) {\\n                        break;\\n                    }\\n                    spf[i * p] = p;\\n                }\\n            }\\n            return primes;\\n        };\\n    \\n        const auto\\u0026 primes = linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(sqrt(*max_element(cbegin(nums), cend(nums))));\\n        unordered_map\\u003cint, int\\u003e lookup;\\n        const auto\\u0026 count_of_distinct_prime_factors = [\\u0026](int x) {\\n            const int y = x;\\n            if (!lookup.count(y)) {\\n                int cnt = 0;\\n                for (const auto\\u0026 p : primes) {\\n                    if (p * p \\u003e x) {\\n                        break;\\n                    }\\n                    if (x % p != 0) {\\n                        continue;\\n                    }\\n                    ++cnt;\\n                    for (; x % p == 0; x /= p);\\n                }\\n                if (x != 1) {\\n                    ++cnt;\\n                }\\n                lookup[y] = cnt;\\n            }\\n            return lookup[y];\\n        };\\n\\n        vector\\u003cint\\u003e scores;\\n        scores.reserve(size(nums));\\n        for (const auto\\u0026 x : nums) {\\n            scores.emplace_back(count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x));\\n        }\\n\\n        vector\\u003cint\\u003e stk = {-1};\\n        vector\\u003cint\\u003e left(size(scores), -1);\\n        for (int i = 0; i \\u003c size(scores); ++i) {\\n            while (stk.back() != -1 \\u0026\\u0026 scores[stk.back()] \\u003c scores[i]) {  // if multiple such elements exist, choose the one with the smallest index\\n                stk.pop_back();\\n            }\\n            left[i] = stk.back();\\n            stk.emplace_back(i);\\n        }\\n        stk = {static_cast\\u003cint\\u003e(size(scores))};\\n        vector\\u003cint\\u003e right(size(scores), -1);\\n        for (int i =  size(scores) - 1; i \\u003e= 0; --i) {\\n            while (stk.back() != size(scores) \\u0026\\u0026 scores[stk.back()] \\u003c= scores[i]) {\\n                stk.pop_back();\\n            }\\n            right[i] = stk.back();\\n            stk.emplace_back(i);\\n        }\\n\\n        int result = 1;\\n        vector\\u003cpair\\u003cint, int\\u003e\\u003e pairs;\\n        pairs.reserve(size(nums));\\n        for (int i = 0; i \\u003c size(nums); ++i) {\\n            pairs.emplace_back(nums[i], i);\\n        }\\n        priority_queue\\u003cpair\\u003cint, int\\u003e\\u003e max_heap(cbegin(pairs), cend(pairs));\\n        while (!empty(max_heap)) {\\n            const auto [_, i] = max_heap.top(); max_heap.pop();\\n            const int c = min((i - left[i]) * (right[i] - i), k);\\n            result = mulmod(result, powmod(nums[i], c));\\n            k -= c;\\n            if (!k) {\\n                break;\\n            }\\n        }\\n        return result;\\n    }\\n};\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"23:Tac1,\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"# Time:  O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + pi(sqrt(r))) + klogn) = O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), m is max(k for _, k in queries), pi(n) = number of primes in a range [1, n] = O(n/logn) by prime number theorem, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number_theorem\\n# Space: O(sqrt(r) + n)\\n\\nimport heapq\\n\\n\\n# number theory, mono stack, greedy, sort, heap\\nclass Solution(object):\\n    def maximumScore(self, nums, k):\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        :type nums: List[int]\\n        :type k: int\\n        :rtype: int\\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"\\n        MOD = 10**9+7\\n        def linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(n):  # Time: O(n), Space: O(n)\\n            primes = []\\n            spf = [-1]*(n+1)  # the smallest prime factor\\n            for i in xrange(2, n+1):\\n                if spf[i] == -1:\\n                    spf[i] = i\\n                    primes.append(i)\\n                for p in primes:\\n                    if i*p \\u003e n or p \\u003e spf[i]:\\n                        break\\n                    spf[i*p] = p\\n            return primes  # len(primes) = O(n/(logn-1)), reference: https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/264544/how-to-find-number-of-prime-numbers-up-to-to-n\\n\\n\\n        lookup = {}\\n        def count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x):\\n            y = x\\n            if y not in lookup:\\n                cnt = 0\\n                for p in primes:\\n                    if p*p \\u003e x:\\n                        break\\n                    if x%p != 0:\\n                        continue\\n                    cnt += 1\\n                    while x%p == 0:\\n                        x //= p\\n                if x != 1:\\n                    cnt += 1\\n                lookup[y] = cnt\\n            return lookup[y]\\n\\n        primes = linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(int(max(nums)**0.5))\\n        scores = [count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x) for x in nums]\\n\\n        left = [-1]*len(scores)\\n        stk = [-1]\\n        for i in xrange(len(scores)):\\n            while stk[-1] != -1 and scores[stk[-1]] \\u003c scores[i]:  # if multiple such elements exist, choose the one with the smallest index\\n                stk.pop()\\n            left[i] = stk[-1]\\n            stk.append(i)\\n        right = [-1]*len(scores)\\n        stk = [len(scores)]\\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(scores))):\\n            while stk[-1] != len(scores) and scores[stk[-1]] \\u003c= scores[i]:\\n                stk.pop()\\n            right[i] = stk[-1]\\n            stk.append(i)\\n        \\n        result = 1\\n        max_heap = [(-x, i) for i, x in enumerate(nums)]\\n        heapq.heapify(max_heap)\\n        while max_heap:\\n            _, i = heapq.heappop(max_heap)\\n            c = min((i-left[i])*(right[i]-i), k)\\n            result = (result*pow(nums[i], c, MOD))%MOD\\n            k -= c\\n            if not k:\\n                break\\n        return result\\n\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"1f:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"article\\\",null,{\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"header\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"space-y-4\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"#\\\",2818]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-hard/15 text-hard\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Hard\\\"}],false,[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"~\\\",50,\\\" min\\\"]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h1\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"p\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"Time \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)\\\"}],\\\" · \\\",\\\"Space \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"strong\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"O(sqrt(r) + n)\\\"}],\\\" · \\\",[\\\"$\\\",\\\"a\\\",null,{\\\"href\\\":\\\"https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\\\",\\\"target\\\":\\\"_blank\\\",\\\"rel\\\":\\\"noopener noreferrer\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Official statement on LeetCode\\\"}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"binary-heap\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/topics/binary-heap\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"binary heap\\\"}]}]],[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"stack\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/stack\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"stack\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"greedy\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/greedy\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"greedy\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"sort\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/sort\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"sort\\\"}]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"heap\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/patterns/heap\\\",\\\"children\\\":[\\\"$\\\",\\\"span\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"heap\\\"}]}]],[]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L20\\\",null,{\\\"slug\\\":\\\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\"}],[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"cpp\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/cpp\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"cpp\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L3\\\",\\\"python\\\",{\\\"href\\\":\\\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/python\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"python\\\"}]]]}]]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10\\\",\\\"id\\\":\\\"solutions\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Solutions\\\"}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"$L21\\\",null,{\\\"solutions\\\":{\\\"cpp\\\":{\\\"language\\\":\\\"C++\\\",\\\"languageSlug\\\":\\\"cpp\\\",\\\"filename\\\":\\\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score.cpp\\\",\\\"code\\\":\\\"$22\\\",\\\"sourcePath\\\":\\\"C++/apply-operations-to-maximize-score.cpp\\\"},\\\"python\\\":{\\\"language\\\":\\\"Python\\\",\\\"languageSlug\\\":\\\"python\\\",\\\"filename\\\":\\\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score.py\\\",\\\"code\\\":\\\"$23\\\",\\\"sourcePath\\\":\\\"Python/apply-operations-to-maximize-score.py\\\"}}}]]}],[\\\"$L24\\\",\\\"$L25\\\",\\\"$L26\\\",\\\"$L27\\\",\\\"$L28\\\",\\\"$L29\\\",\\\"$L2a\\\",\\\"$L2b\\\",\\\"$L2c\\\",\\\"$L2d\\\"],\\\"$L2e\\\",\\\"$L2f\\\",\\\"$L30\\\",\\\"$L31\\\",\\\"$L32\\\",\\\"$L33\\\"]}],\\\"$L34\\\"]}]\\n\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"3d:I[203221,[\\\"/_next/static/chunks/2fvm6eoqeukxu.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/1ntn7efqc-iiw.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/0plpm2axnqe9k.js\\\",\\\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\\\"],\\\"ConfidenceTracker\\\"]\\n35:T438,\\u003ch2\\u003eWhat is Apply Operations to Maximize Score?\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eApply Operations to Maximize Score\\u003c/strong\\u003e (LeetCode #2818) is a \\u003cstrong\\u003eHard\\u003c/strong\\u003e problem that primarily trains \\u003cstrong\\u003ebinary heap\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eHow to think about it\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eRestate the goal\\u003c/strong\\u003e in your own words before coding.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eWork a \\u003cstrong\\u003etiny example\\u003c/strong\\u003e by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eIdentify the \\u003cstrong\\u003epattern\\u003c/strong\\u003e — this problem aligns with \\u003cstrong\\u003estack, greedy, sort, and heap\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eOnly then translate the idea into code.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eWhy this problem matters\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eHard problems force you to combine patterns and prove complexity carefully — interview gold.\\nOfficial solution notes mention: Number Theory, Linear Sieve of Eratosthenes, Mono Stack, Greedy.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003cblockquote\\u003e\\n\\u003cp\\u003eAlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the \\u003ca href=\\\"https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\\\"\\u003eofficial problem statement on LeetCode\\u003c/a\\u003e for constraints and examples.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\n\\u003c/blockquote\\u003e\\n24:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"beginner\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"beginner\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Beginner Explanation\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$35\\\"}}]]}]\\n36:T50e,\\u003ch2\\u003eInterview approach for Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eOpening (30–60 seconds)\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eClarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eState a \\u003cstrong\\u003ebrute force\\u003c/strong\\u003e so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003ePropose the \\u003cstrong\\u003eoptimal direction\\u003c/strong\\u003e tied to \\u003cstrong\\u003estack, greedy, sort, and heap\\u003c/strong\\u003e.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eCore solution narrative\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eDefine the \\u003cstrong\\u003estate\\u003c/strong\\u003e you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eExplain the \\u003cstrong\\u003etransition\\u003c/strong\\u003e when you process the next element.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCall out \\u003cstrong\\u003etime\\u003c/strong\\u003e (O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)) and \\u003cstrong\\u003espace\\u003c/strong\\u003e (O(sqrt(r) + n)) before coding.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCode cleanly; narrate variable names.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ol\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eWhat interviewers listen for\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCorrectness on edge cases\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eComplexity honesty\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eAbility to discuss \\u003cstrong\\u003etrade-offs\\u003c/strong\\u003e (e.g., hash map space vs. sort + two pointers)\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eFollow-up questions they may ask\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eCan you solve it with less memory?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eWhat if the input stream is infinite / doesn't fit in RAM?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003cli\\u003eHow would tests look for adversarial inputs?\\u003c/li\\u003e\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\n25:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"interview\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"interview\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Interview Walkthrough\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"$36\\\"}}]]}]\\n26:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"optimized\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"optimized\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Optimized Approach\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003ch2\\u003eOptimized solution notes\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cp\\u003eThe reference solutions on AlgoForge target \\u003cstrong\\u003eO(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)\\u003c/strong\\u003e time and \\u003cstrong\\u003eO(sqrt(r) + n)\\u003c/strong\\u003e space.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ch3\\u003ePattern focus: stack, greedy, sort, and heap\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cp\\u003eUse the pattern as a checklist:\\u003c/p\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003estack\\u003c/strong\\u003e — confirm the invariant holds after each step\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003egreedy\\u003c/strong\\u003e — confirm the invariant holds after each step\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003esort\"])</script><script>self.__next_f.push([1,\"\\u003c/strong\\u003e — confirm the invariant holds after each step\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eheap\\u003c/strong\\u003e — confirm the invariant holds after each step\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cp\\u003eMultiple methods appear in the source solutions — compare them and explain when each is preferable.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eImplementation tips\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003ePrefer readable names over micro-optimizations in interviews.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003eExtract helpers only when they clarify (e.g., expand-around-center, DFS visit).\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003eAfter AC-level logic, re-scan for off-by-one and null checks.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\\\n\\\"}}]]}]\\n27:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"complexity\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"complexity\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Complexity Analysis\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003ch2\\u003eComplexity\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctable\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cthead\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cth\\u003eMeasure\\u003c/th\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cth\\u003eBound\\u003c/th\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/tr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/thead\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctbody\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctd\\u003eTime\\u003c/td\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctd\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eO(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/td\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/tr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctd\\u003eSpace\\u003c/td\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ctd\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eO(sqrt(r) + n)\\u003c/strong\\u003e\\u003c/td\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/tr\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/tbody\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/table\\u003e\\\\n\\u003ch3\\u003eHow to justify this in an interview\\u003c/h3\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cul\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eTime:\\u003c/strong\\u003e count loops, map/set operations, and recursive branching; state average vs worst case if relevant.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eSpace:\\u003c/strong\\u003e include hash maps, recursion stack, and output allocation when the problem asks for it.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003c/ul\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cp\\u003eIf your implementation differs from the reference, re-derive big-O from \\u003cem\\u003eyour\\u003c/em\\u003e code — never memorize a complexity you cannot defend.\\u003c/p\\u003e\\\\n\\\"}}]]}]\\n28:[\\\"$\\\",\\\"section\\\",\\\"common-mistakes\\\",{\\\"id\\\":\\\"common-mistakes\\\",\\\"className\\\":\\\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\\\",\\\"children\\\":[[\\\"$\\\",\\\"h2\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"text-xl font-bold\\\",\\\"children\\\":\\\"Common Mistakes\\\"}],false]}],[\\\"$\\\",\\\"div\\\",null,{\\\"className\\\":\\\"prose-af\\\",\\\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\\\":{\\\"__html\\\":\\\"\\u003ch2\\u003eCommon mistakes on Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\u003c/h2\\u003e\\\\n\\u003col\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eSkipping edge cases\\u003c/strong\\u003e — empty collections, single-element inputs, max constraints.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eWrong invariant\\u003c/strong\\u003e for stack, greedy, sort, and heap — updating state too early or too late.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eMutating input unexpectedly\\u003c/strong\\u003e when the problem forbids it.\\u003c/li\\u003e\\\\n\\u003cli\\u003e\\u003cstrong\\u003eOff-by-one\\u003c/strong\\u003e in window