pply Operations to Maximize Score good for interviews?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — as a Hard problem it is a solid practice target. Pair it with related problems in the same pattern family for spaced repetition.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Where can I read the official statement?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Open the official LeetCode page for constraints and examples: https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\"}}]}0:{\"rsc\":[\"$\",\"$1\",\"c\",{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"container-af py-8\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Article\\\",\\\"headline\\\":\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Hard explanation for Apply Operations to Maximize Score (LeetCode #2818). Pattern: stack. Time O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), space O(sqrt(r) + n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"url\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\",\\\"author\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"publisher\\\":{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"Organization\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"AlgoForge\\\"},\\\"datePublished\\\":\\\"2026-01-01\\\",\\\"dateModified\\\":\\\"2026-07-17\\\"}\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$2\"}}],[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowTo\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"How to solve Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\",\\\"description\\\":\\\"Original Hard explanation for Apply Operations to Maximize Score (LeetCode #2818). Pattern: stack. Time O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), space O(sqrt(r) + n). Multi-language solutions and interview tips.\\\",\\\"step\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Read the official problem statement on LeetCode\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Solve on paper / whiteboard first\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Implement the stack, greedy, sort, and heap approach\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":4,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Verify edge cases from the checklist\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":5,\\\"text\\\":\\\"State time and space complexity aloud\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":6,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Compare with the AlgoForge reference solution\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"HowToStep\\\",\\\"position\\\":7,\\\"text\\\":\\\"Schedule a revision session\\\"}]}\"}}],[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"script\",null,{\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Problems\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://algoforge.dev/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\\\"}]}\"}}],\"$L3\"]}],\"$L4\"]}],[\"$L5\"],\"$L6\"]}],\"isPartial\":false,\"staleTime\":300,\"varyParams\":null,\"buildId\":\"qYmpHdIWGSv0ZBoY8Y0Bn\"}\n3:[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[false,[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Home\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",null,{\"href\":\"/problems\",\"className\":\"hover:text-primary transition-colors\",\"children\":\"Problems\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-1.5\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"aria-hidden\":true,\"className\":\"text-border\",\"children\":\"/\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground font-medium\",\"aria-current\":\"page\",\"children\":\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\"}]]}]]}]\na:T11a6,// Time:  O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + pi(sqrt(r))) + klogn) = O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), m is max(k for _, k in queries), pi(n) = number of primes in a range [1, n] = O(n/logn) by prime number theorem, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number_theorem\n// Space: O(sqrt(r) + n)\n\n// number theory, mono stack, greedy, sort, heap\nclass Solution {\npublic:\n    int maximumScore(vector<int>& nums, int k) {\n        static const int MOD = 1e9 + 7;\n        const auto& addmod = [&](uint32_t a, uint32_t b) {  // avoid overflow\n            a %= MOD, b %= MOD;\n            if (MOD - a <= b) {\n                b -= MOD;  // relied on unsigned integer overflow in order to give the expected results\n            }\n            return a + b;\n        };\n\n        const auto& mulmod = [&](uint32_t a, uint32_t b)  {  // avoid overflow\n            a %= MOD, b %= MOD;\n            uint32_t result = 0;\n            if (a < b) {\n                swap(a, b);\n            }\n            while (b > 0)  { \n                if (b % 2 == 1) {\n                    result = addmod(result, a);\n                }\n                a = addmod(a, a);\n                b /= 2; \n            } \n            return result; \n        };\n\n        const auto& powmod = [&](uint32_t a, uint32_t b) {\n            a %= MOD;\n            uint32_t result = 1;\n            while (b) {\n                if (b & 1) {\n                    result = mulmod(result, a);\n                }\n                a = mulmod(a, a);\n                b >>= 1;\n            }\n            return result;\n        };\n    \n        const auto& linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes = [](int n) {  // Time: O(n), Space: O(n)\n            vector<int> spf(n + 1, -1);\n            vector<int> primes;\n            for (int i = 2; i <= n; ++i) {\n                if (spf[i] == -1) {\n                    spf[i] = i;\n                    primes.emplace_back(i);\n                }\n                for (const auto& p : primes) {\n                    if (i * p > n || p > spf[i]) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    spf[i * p] = p;\n                }\n            }\n            return primes;\n        };\n    \n        const auto& primes = linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(sqrt(*max_element(cbegin(nums), cend(nums))));\n        unordered_map<int, int> lookup;\n        const auto& count_of_distinct_prime_factors = [&](int x) {\n            const int y = x;\n            if (!lookup.count(y)) {\n                int cnt = 0;\n                for (const auto& p : primes) {\n                    if (p * p > x) {\n                        break;\n                    }\n                    if (x % p != 0) {\n                        continue;\n                    }\n                    ++cnt;\n                    for (; x % p == 0; x /= p);\n                }\n                if (x != 1) {\n                    ++cnt;\n                }\n                lookup[y] = cnt;\n            }\n            return lookup[y];\n        };\n\n        vector<int> scores;\n        scores.reserve(size(nums));\n        for (const auto& x : nums) {\n            scores.emplace_back(count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x));\n        }\n\n        vector<int> stk = {-1};\n        vector<int> left(size(scores), -1);\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(scores); ++i) {\n            while (stk.back() != -1 && scores[stk.back()] < scores[i]) {  // if multiple such elements exist, choose the one with the smallest index\n                stk.pop_back();\n            }\n            left[i] = stk.back();\n            stk.emplace_back(i);\n        }\n        stk = {static_cast<int>(size(scores))};\n        vector<int> right(size(scores), -1);\n        for (int i =  size(scores) - 1; i >= 0; --i) {\n            while (stk.back() != size(scores) && scores[stk.back()] <= scores[i]) {\n                stk.pop_back();\n            }\n            right[i] = stk.back();\n            stk.emplace_back(i);\n        }\n\n        int result = 1;\n        vector<pair<int, int>> pairs;\n        pairs.reserve(size(nums));\n        for (int i = 0; i < size(nums); ++i) {\n            pairs.emplace_back(nums[i], i);\n        }\n        priority_queue<pair<int, int>> max_heap(cbegin(pairs), cend(pairs));\n        while (!empty(max_heap)) {\n            const auto [_, i] = max_heap.top(); max_heap.pop();\n            const int c = min((i - left[i]) * (right[i] - i), k);\n            result = mulmod(result, powmod(nums[i], c));\n            k -= c;\n            if (!k) {\n                break;\n            }\n        }\n        return result;\n    }\n};\nb:Tac1,# Time:  O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + pi(sqrt(r))) + klogn) = O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn), m is max(k for _, k in queries), pi(n) = number of primes in a range [1, n] = O(n/logn) by prime number theorem, see https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prime_number_theorem\n# Space: O(sqrt(r) + n)\n\nimport heapq\n\n\n# number theory, mono stack, greedy, sort, heap\nclass Solution(object):\n    def maximumScore(self, nums, k):\n        \"\"\"\n        :type nums: List[int]\n        :type k: int\n        :rtype: int\n        \"\"\"\n        MOD = 10**9+7\n        def linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(n):  # Time: O(n), Space: O(n)\n            primes = []\n            spf = [-1]*(n+1)  # the smallest prime factor\n            for i in xrange(2, n+1):\n                if spf[i] == -1:\n                    spf[i] = i\n                    primes.append(i)\n                for p in primes:\n                    if i*p > n or p > spf[i]:\n                        break\n                    spf[i*p] = p\n            return primes  # len(primes) = O(n/(logn-1)), reference: https://math.stackexchange.com/questions/264544/how-to-find-number-of-prime-numbers-up-to-to-n\n\n\n        lookup = {}\n        def count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x):\n            y = x\n            if y not in lookup:\n                cnt = 0\n                for p in primes:\n                    if p*p > x:\n                        break\n                    if x%p != 0:\n                        continue\n                    cnt += 1\n                    while x%p == 0:\n                        x //= p\n                if x != 1:\n                    cnt += 1\n                lookup[y] = cnt\n            return lookup[y]\n\n        primes = linear_sieve_of_eratosthenes(int(max(nums)**0.5))\n        scores = [count_of_distinct_prime_factors(x) for x in nums]\n\n        left = [-1]*len(scores)\n        stk = [-1]\n        for i in xrange(len(scores)):\n            while stk[-1] != -1 and scores[stk[-1]] < scores[i]:  # if multiple such elements exist, choose the one with the smallest index\n                stk.pop()\n            left[i] = stk[-1]\n            stk.append(i)\n        right = [-1]*len(scores)\n        stk = [len(scores)]\n        for i in reversed(xrange(len(scores))):\n            while stk[-1] != len(scores) and scores[stk[-1]] <= scores[i]:\n                stk.pop()\n            right[i] = stk[-1]\n            stk.append(i)\n        \n        result = 1\n        max_heap = [(-x, i) for i, x in enumerate(nums)]\n        heapq.heapify(max_heap)\n        while max_heap:\n            _, i = heapq.heappop(max_heap)\n            c = min((i-left[i])*(right[i]-i), k)\n            result = (result*pow(nums[i], c, MOD))%MOD\n            k -= c\n            if not k:\n                break\n        return result\n\n4:[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-6 grid lg:grid-cols-[1fr_280px] gap-10\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"article\",null,{\"children\":[[\"$\",\"header\",null,{\"className\":\"space-y-4\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-sm text-muted-foreground tabular-nums\",\"children\":[\"#\",2818]}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-hard/15 text-hard\",\"children\":\"Hard\"}],false,[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":[\"~\",50,\" min\"]}]]}],[\"$\",\"h1\",null,{\"className\":\"text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight\",\"children\":\"Apply Operations to Maximize Score\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"text-muted-foreground max-w-2xl\",\"children\":[\"Time \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)\"}],\" · \",\"Space \",[\"$\",\"strong\",null,{\"className\":\"text-foreground\",\"children\":\"O(sqrt(r) + n)\"}],\" · \",[\"$\",\"a\",null,{\"href\":\"https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\",\"target\":\"_blank\",\"rel\":\"noopener noreferrer\",\"className\":\"text-primary underline-offset-2 hover:underline\",\"children\":\"Official statement on LeetCode\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\",\"children\":[[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"binary-heap\",{\"href\":\"/topics/binary-heap\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide bg-primary/15 text-primary\",\"children\":\"binary heap\"}]}]],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"stack\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/stack\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"stack\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"greedy\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/greedy\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"greedy\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"sort\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/sort\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"sort\"}]}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"heap\",{\"href\":\"/patterns/heap\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"inline-flex items-center rounded-full px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold tracking-wide border border-border text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"heap\"}]}]],[]]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap gap-2 pt-1\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L8\",null,{\"slug\":\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score\"}],[[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"cpp\",{\"href\":\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/cpp\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"cpp\"}],[\"$\",\"$L7\",\"python\",{\"href\":\"/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/python\",\"className\":\"text-sm text-primary hover:underline\",\"children\":\"python\"}]]]}]]}],[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"mt-10\",\"id\":\"solutions\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Solutions\"}],[\"$\",\"$L9\",null,{\"solutions\":{\"cpp\":{\"language\":\"C++\",\"languageSlug\":\"cpp\",\"filename\":\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score.cpp\",\"code\":\"$a\",\"sourcePath\":\"C++/apply-operations-to-maximize-score.cpp\"},\"python\":{\"language\":\"Python\",\"languageSlug\":\"python\",\"filename\":\"apply-operations-to-maximize-score.py\",\"code\":\"$b\",\"sourcePath\":\"Python/apply-operations-to-maximize-score.py\"}}}]]}],[\"$Lc\",\"$Ld\",\"$Le\",\"$Lf\",\"$L10\",\"$L11\",\"$L12\",\"$L13\",\"$L14\",\"$L15\"],\"$L16\",\"$L17\",\"$L18\",\"$L19\",\"$L1a\",\"$L1b\"]}],\"$L1c\"]}]\n5:[\"$\",\"script\",\"script-0\",{\"src\":\"/_next/static/chunks/259rkrk9l2f9c.js\",\"async\":true}]\n6:[\"$\",\"$L1d\",null,{\"children\":[\"$\",\"$1e\",null,{\"name\":\"Next.MetadataOutlet\",\"children\":\"$@1f\"}]}]\n20:T438,<h2>What is Apply Operations to Maximize Score?</h2>\n<p><strong>Apply Operations to Maximize Score</strong> (LeetCode #2818) is a <strong>Hard</strong> problem that primarily trains <strong>binary heap</strong>.</p>\n<h3>How to think about it</h3>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Restate the goal</strong> in your own words before coding.</li>\n<li>Work a <strong>tiny example</strong> by hand so the invariant becomes obvious.</li>\n<li>Identify the <strong>pattern</strong> — this problem aligns with <strong>stack, greedy, sort, and heap</strong>.</li>\n<li>Only then translate the idea into code.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>Why this problem matters</h3>\n<p>Hard problems force you to combine patterns and prove complexity carefully — interview gold.\nOfficial solution notes mention: Number Theory, Linear Sieve of Eratosthenes, Mono Stack, Greedy.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>AlgoForge explanations are original teaching notes. Always open the <a href=\"https://leetcode.com/problems/apply-operations-to-maximize-score/\">official problem statement on LeetCode</a> for constraints and examples.</p>\n</blockquote>\nc:[\"$\",\"section\",\"beginner\",{\"id\":\"beginner\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Beginner Explanation\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$20\"}}]]}]\n21:T50e,<h2>Interview approach for Apply Operations to Maximize Score</h2>\n<h3>Opening (30–60 seconds)</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clarify inputs/outputs and edge cases (empty input, single element, duplicates, overflow).</li>\n<li>State a <strong>brute force</strong> so the interviewer knows you can solve it naively.</li>\n<li>Propose the <strong>optimal direction</strong> tied to <strong>stack, greedy, sort, and heap</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Core solution narrative</h3>\n<ol>\n<li>Define the <strong>state</strong> you track (pointers, DP cell, set membership, stack top, etc.).</li>\n<li>Explain the <strong>transition</strong> when you process the next element.</li>\n<li>Call out <strong>time</strong> (O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)) and <strong>space</strong> (O(sqrt(r) + n)) before coding.</li>\n<li>Code cleanly; narrate variable names.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>What interviewers listen for</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Correctness on edge cases</li>\n<li>Complexity honesty</li>\n<li>Ability to discuss <strong>trade-offs</strong> (e.g., hash map space vs. sort + two pointers)</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Follow-up questions they may ask</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Can you solve it with less memory?</li>\n<li>What if the input stream is infinite / doesn't fit in RAM?</li>\n<li>How would tests look for adversarial inputs?</li>\n</ul>\nd:[\"$\",\"section\",\"interview\",{\"id\":\"interview\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Interview Walkthrough\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$21\"}}]]}]\ne:[\"$\",\"section\",\"optimized\",{\"id\":\"optimized\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Optimized Approach\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Optimized solution notes</h2>\\n<p>The reference solutions on AlgoForge target <strong>O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)</strong> time and <strong>O(sqrt(r) + n)</strong> space.</p>\\n<h3>Pattern focus: stack, greedy, sort, and heap</h3>\\n<p>Use the pattern as a checklist:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>stack</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n<li><strong>greedy</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n<li><strong>sort</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n<li><strong>heap</strong> — confirm the invariant holds after each step</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Multiple methods appear in the source solutions — compare them and explain when each is preferable.</p>\\n<h3>Implementation tips</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Prefer readable names over micro-optimizations in interviews.</li>\\n<li>Extract helpers only when they clarify (e.g., expand-around-center, DFS visit).</li>\\n<li>After AC-level logic, re-scan for off-by-one and null checks.</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\nf:[\"$\",\"section\",\"complexity\",{\"id\":\"complexity\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Complexity Analysis\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Complexity</h2>\\n<table>\\n<thead>\\n<tr>\\n<th>Measure</th>\\n<th>Bound</th>\\n</tr>\\n</thead>\\n<tbody>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Time</td>\\n<td><strong>O(sqrt(r) + n * (logr + sqrt(r)/log(sqrt(r))) + klogn)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n<tr>\\n<td>Space</td>\\n<td><strong>O(sqrt(r) + n)</strong></td>\\n</tr>\\n</tbody>\\n</table>\\n<h3>How to justify this in an interview</h3>\\n<ul>\\n<li><strong>Time:</strong> count loops, map/set operations, and recursive branching; state average vs worst case if relevant.</li>\\n<li><strong>Space:</strong> include hash maps, recursion stack, and output allocation when the problem asks for it.</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>If your implementation differs from the reference, re-derive big-O from <em>your</em> code — never memorize a complexity you cannot defend.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n10:[\"$\",\"section\",\"common-mistakes\",{\"id\":\"common-mistakes\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Common Mistakes\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Common mistakes on Apply Operations to Maximize Score</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Skipping edge cases</strong> — empty collections, single-element inputs, max constraints.</li>\\n<li><strong>Wrong invariant</strong> for stack, greedy, sort, and heap — updating state too early or too late.</li>\\n<li><strong>Mutating input unexpectedly</strong> when the problem forbids it.</li>\\n<li><strong>Off-by-one</strong> in windows, ranges, or binary search bounds.</li>\\n<li><strong>Ignoring overflow / precision</strong> for integer arithmetic problems.</li>\\n<li><strong>Overengineering</strong> — jumping to an advanced structure when a simpler approach works.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n11:[\"$\",\"section\",\"alternatives\",{\"id\":\"alternatives\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Alternative Approaches\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Alternatives</h2>\\n<p>The source file includes more than one method. Compare:</p>\\n<ol>\\n<li><strong>Primary optimized path</strong> — best complexity for typical interviews.</li>\\n<li><strong>Secondary approach</strong> — often brute force, sorting-based, or space-optimized variant.</li>\\n</ol>\\n<p>Practice articulating <strong>when</strong> you would pick each (constraints, readability, follow-ups).</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n12:[\"$\",\"section\",\"edge-cases\",{\"id\":\"edge-cases\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Edge Cases\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Edge cases checklist</h2>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Minimum input size</li>\\n<li>Maximum input size / time limits</li>\\n<li>Duplicates and already-sorted input</li>\\n<li>Negative numbers / zeros (if applicable)</li>\\n<li>Disconnected structures (graphs/trees)</li>\\n<li>Single path vs branching recursion depth</li>\\n</ul>\\n\"}}]]}]\n13:[\"$\",\"section\",\"pattern-recognition\",{\"id\":\"pattern-recognition\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Pattern Recognition\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Spotting this pattern</h2>\\n<p>Signal phrases that point to <strong>stack, greedy, sort, and heap</strong>:</p>\\n<ul>\\n<li>Sorted input or ability to sort without changing the answer class</li>\\n<li>Need for contiguous subarray / substring → consider sliding window</li>\\n<li>Need for O(1) membership → hash set/map</li>\\n<li>Optimal substructure + overlapping subproblems → DP</li>\\n<li>Connectivity / components → graph DFS/BFS or Union-Find</li>\\n</ul>\\n<p>Primary topics: <strong>binary heap</strong>.</p>\\n\"}}]]}]\n14:[\"$\",\"section\",\"follow-ups\",{\"id\":\"follow-ups\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Follow-up Interview Questions\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>Follow-ups</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>How does the solution change if the input is a stream?</li>\\n<li>Can you solve it in-place?</li>\\n<li>What if duplicates must be handled differently?</li>\\n<li>How would you parallelize the approach?</li>\\n<li>Design tests that would break a buggy implementation.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n15:[\"$\",\"section\",\"practice\",{\"id\":\"practice\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2 mb-3\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold\",\"children\":\"Practice Recommendations\"}],false]}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"prose-af\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"<h2>What to practice next</h2>\\n<ol>\\n<li>Re-solve <strong>Apply Operations to Maximize Score</strong> in a second language (cpp, python).</li>\\n<li>Drill 3–5 more problems tagged <strong>binary heap</strong>.</li>\\n<li>Teach the solution out loud in under 5 minutes.</li>\\n<li>Add this problem to your revision calendar in 3 days and 14 days.</li>\\n</ol>\\n\"}}]]}]\n16:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"id\":\"visualization\",\"className\":\"mt-10 scroll-mt-24\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"h2\",null,{\"className\":\"text-xl font-bold mb-3\",\"children\":\"Visualization\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-xl border border-dashed border-border bg-muted/40 p-6 text-sm text-muted-foreground\",\"children\":\"Conceptual diagram for Apply Operations to Maximize Score: show input st